.htaccess filename:
IndexIgnore filename1,filename2,...


How to hide folder or file from indexing in Apache:
By default out of security concern few files and folder in Apache is redirected to appear 
in indexing .
such files header.php and public_html...etc in server configuration.

such configuration can be modified using .htaccess
indexIgnore *
where * is a wild card charecter for disabling all indexing .

Note:Its write the .htaccess file then its working
Ignoring any folder or files :
IndexIgnore folder_name or files_name
indexIgnore *.php
Example:
IndexIgnore file-uploading

How to protect directory access:
options -Indexes:To disable indexing
options +Indexes:To enable indexing

(inside the vhost.conf)

How to modify server configuration without using .htaccess:
We have to use server confoguration using virtual host.
goto c://xampp/apache/conf/extra/https.vhosts

<virtualhost *:port_number>
DocumentRoot "path/to/your/files"
<Directory 'path_of_particular_file_or_folder(or absolutepath)'>
  Deny from all(to hide the particular file which u donot want to show the user)
</Directory>
</virtualhost>

How to disable a folder from accessing but allow for indexing:
<virtualhost *:port_number>
DocumentRoot "path/to/your/files"
<Directory 'path_of_particular_file_or_folder(or absolutepath)'>
  optiona -Indexes(to hide the functionnality of a particular file which u donot want
  to show the user)
</Directory>
</virtualhost>

Example:
<VirtualHost *:8000>
    DocumentRoot "C:/xampp/htdocs"
	<Directory "C:\xampp\htdocs\php-class">
	   Deny from all
	</Directory>

</VirtualHost>
