Sanitisation:
----
Xss filtering:Preventing user or hacker from injecting any other script such that it donot 
enables php to execute.
XSS Means cross site scripting.
remove tag:
strip_tags();
remove executuion of tags:
htmlspecialchars()
remove html entities:(&copy is a entity)
htmlentities()
html_entities_decode()
                               
Sometimes you may required tags and may not required tags:
Example:
<h1>Hello</h1>from text box when submitted heading tag with hello.

in such case we need to remove tags:
strip_tags() remove the tag.

In some case charecters are not required then form remove the entities use below function:
htmlentities() prevents from generating html entities.

if you want to generate it:
html_entity_decode();

in some cases you may require tag for generate presentation use htmlspecialchars() which 
automatically converts tags to special charecters set such that all the code is printed
in raw formate.

Make a user defined function to perform XSS Filtering:
function sanitise($arg){
$arg=strip_tags($arg);
$arg=htmlentities($arg);
$arg=htmlspecialchars($arg);
$arg=trim($arg);
return $arg;
}


WAP for small blog application where user can post its php codes based on topics.
<?php 

?>
<html>
<head></head>
<body>
<h1>PHP Blogs:</h1>
<form action="" method="post">
Title:<br/><input type="text" name="title"/><br/>
Description:<textarea name="content"></textarea><br/><br/>
<input type="submit" name="btn">
</form>
</body>
</html>

<?php
$title=strip_tags($_POST['title']);
$content=$_POST['content'];


echo "<h1>".htmlentities(trim($title))."</h1>";
echo "<hr/>";
echo htmlspecialchars($content);


?>

